**Create MySQL Database**

Customer can create new MySQL database from their client portal. To do that go to **Menu** >> **Databases** >> click on **Create MySQL database**.

Write the Database name, Database username, Password for database in the form and submit it.

**Create Backup**

To create a mysql database backup on a shared hosting you can follow the steps given below.

Login to Client Portal from https://www.serverpointapps.com/
Go to **Menu** » **Databases**
Click on the database named for which you need to create the backup
Under the "**Backup**" tab Click on **Request a one time snapshot** of this database option
Click on the Confirm tick Mark option to begin backup process and you will get a message “**A backup for this database is now scheduled to begin**”
Once the backup is created it will be stored to your home directory under **/mysql_backups** folder.

**Change Password**

Customer can now reset the mysql database password from their client portal. To do that go to **Menu** >> **Databases** >> click on the database name you want to reset password. 

Under the "**Password**" tab write new password and then submit it.

**Grant Access to other network**

Now customers can open to access other network. To do that go to **Menu** >> **Databases** >> click on the database name you want open acces

Under the **Access** tab write the address in the filed **IP allowed to access**.

Once it is added then the ip address will be listed under **IPs currently allowed**:. Customer can delete it when they wanted it. Just click on **Delete** button beside the allowed ip address.
